article.description: Nate Wolters scored 25 points and dished out nine assists and South Dakota State upset Iowa 79-69 on Sunday, spoiling coach Fran McCaffery's debut.
article.headline: South Dakota State upsets Iowa in season opener
article.linkText: S. Dakota St. spoils debut of Iowa's McCaffery
article.story: IOWA CITY, Iowa -- Nate Wolters scored 25 points and dished out nine assists and South Dakota State upset Iowa 79-69 on Sunday, spoiling coach Fran McCaffery's debut. Clint Sargent added 16 points for the Jackrabbits (2-0), who handed the Hawkeyes their second-straight loss in an opener. Tony Fiegen hit a layup to put South Dakota State ahead 71-66, and Griffan Callahan buried a jumper from the corner to put the Jackrabbits ahead by seven with 2:25 left. Eric May scored 20 points and Jarryd Cole had 17 points and eight boards for the Hawkeyes, who have dropped two consecutive openers after winning the previous 31.
